task.summary: Still trying to remove files...
Default task
Working on bringing SQL access into server.
Initial creation and population of database done.
Started adding classes for data access
BulletZoneData now provides basic ItemType and ItemCategory information.
Factored out ItemTypeRepository
Started implementing GameItemRepository--needs testing, more creation/update methods.
Item creation works now. Common and Status tables added.
Added some user and permission routines, moved main-testing to BulletZoneData
Changed interface to make more compartmentalized, stuck on user validation now...
User validation now works.
Added Created/Deleted components to Users, Items, BankAccounts, permission correlations, and added new AccountTransferHistory table.
Added methods to add/remove items to/from containers.
Changed server build configuration to include spring framework in .jar file. Note that you may have to run the "bootRepackage" task on the gradle tab to generate it.
Updated the andoirdManifestFile path in build.gradle.
Started adding item deletion. Not tested.
Item deletion is tested, made it so that two users can't be created with the same username.
Made GameItemRepository public
Converted Optionals to use java.util.Optional; added Guava jar to build dependencies.
Added ownership of containers--still not fully tested.
Fixed/tested ownership
Added new permission support (add/remove/use/transfer permissions and permissions caching and checking). New methods not tested, and still need more routines for give/revoking permissions.
Methods to grant/revoke permissions added to PermissionManager, tested minimally.

* Added getUsers() to GameUserRepository * Added type name to initial container name * Added getUserPermissions() to PermissionManager, provided access to internal AccessibleItems class, and added public methods for learning about permissions on items.
* Added new extraLibs line for mariadb so that .jar file builds correctly * Added exception checking in initialization of BulletZoneData so that corrupted databases could more easily be rebuilt.
Added getType method (that accepts a typeID) to ItemTypeRepository.
* Added expansion frames to the database.
Database connections in BulletZoneData are now created and closed as needed, rather than attempting to maintain it throughout.
getPermissions no longer returns null if a user has no permissions.
